ce:section.ce:para:
The surface morphology and average particle size of the CQDs were examined by TEM analysis. The TEM image (Fig. 3
a) revealed that the quantum dots are highly dispersed without any aggregation and exhibit a spherical morphology. The HR-TEM study ( Fig. 3 b) shows lattice fringes with a fringe width of 0.25 nm, which is compatible with the lattice spacing in graphitic carbon atoms [28]. However, the selected area electron diffraction (SAED) pattern reveals that the system as a whole is amorphous ( Fig. 3 c). CQDs have a size distribution between 2 and 6 nm, with an average size of 3.6 nm, according to the particle size histogram in Fig. 3 d. The DLS method suggested a particle size of 7.2 nm, which is close to the particle size measured from the TEM measurements ( Fig. S1
).
